Central bank governorsfrom Spain, Latin America and the Caribbean will meet here thisweek at two separate conmferences to discuss finance andmonetary problems, the Central Bank of Barbados said.    The 24th session of central bank governors of the americancontinent opens today for two days. Central bank governors ofLatin America and Spain will hold a separate conference fromapril 29-30.    Representatives of the Inter American Development Bank, theInternational Monetary Fund and other international financialorganizations will attend both conferences.    The Central Bank of Barbados gave no agenda for themeetings Reuter&#3;